reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Feels and smells wonderful
reviews.reviewText: I bought this shade as a dupe for another lipstick that’s not currently in my budget to purchase and I am so pleased with it! The color matches super well it’s a nude that’s fairly opaque, not drying in any way, smells lightly of vanilla and easy to manipulate to blend. It’s a tad thinner than the formula of the expensive lipstick I’m substituting for but I can work with it as the color payoff for $10 is pretty great.Would purchase again and am now curious about trying other maybelline lipsticks.I believe I purchased the shade fairly nude and it is indeed purely nude. Would recommend for a nude lip look.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Hydrating cream lipstick in nude pink
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this to try on a recommendation by a fashion influencer. I usually use NARS, Bobbie Brown, and Urban Decay brands, but decided to try this drug store brand in Nude Pink based on the reviews. It is a hydrating, cream texture that applies easily and is a very flattering natural color on my medium fair skin tones. (For reference I use Vienna foundation color in NARS brand). It seems very comparable to the higher priced brands and I will be trying additional colors in this very affordable line. Love it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Big approval for Violet Vixen
reviews.reviewText: Okay so this is an amazing color! I tried to capture it after my shower but my bathroom light shows up fairly yellow-tinted. I put this over top of a nude color transfer resistant lip, because I already had it on and it also acts like a lip liner.Instant favorite! I am a lipstick girl and I have more of them than I know what to do with, but I’m so glad I took a chance on this. The nude color underneath tones the violet quite a bit and I can’t wait to try it alone as a more vibrant shade for more pop (maybe when I actually have somewhere to go and I’m not just hanging out in my robe, lol).If you appreciate unique colors in makeup , this is a find for the price. I rate both the quality of color and formulation on par with pricier department store brands. I don’t usually love bullet lipsticks either but Maybelline really brings it with some of their formulations.Also, on a side note, for those with silver hair, I have a feeling this would be really quite lovely! I’m mature in age but still waiting for my silver to grow in. I have light/medium brown hair with a tinge of gray, but is still half wet in this photo so not the best image.

reviews.reviewTitle: A Must-Have Lipstick for Effortless Elegance!
reviews.reviewText: Maybelline's Color Sensational Lipstick is a game-changer! I love this particular as it effortlessly enhance any look. The moisturizing formula keeps my lips hydrated all day. Plus, I love using it as a quick and easy blush—it blends like a dream. I've got one in every purse; it's a must-have for on-the-go beauty!
El color muy bonito , la consistencia muy rica
I use a lot of Maybelline products because I have sensitive skin. These lipsticks were listed as moisturizing, and creamy. I was not disappointed and bought a few more in different colors.
